# Global infrastructure

A set of **nested layers**, each trading **breadth for proximity to the user**.

## Why so many "places" — three pressures

- **Latency** — users are worldwide; the speed of light is fixed
- **Sovereignty** — data has legal homes
- **Failure isolation** — one building's outage can't take you down

## The hierarchy — broad → close

- **Region** — independent geographic area, own data centers. **30+**; runs **all services**
- **Availability Zone** — discrete data centers in a region. **3–6 per region**
- **Edge location** — terminates user connections nearby. **600+**; CloudFront, Route 53, WAF

## Even closer than a Region

**Local Zones** → a metro city · **Wavelength** → a 5G network · **Outposts** → your data center
